Name: SUBMARINE CLASSIFICATION CONFIDENCE LEVEL
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION AND PROBABLE ACCURACY OF THE IDENTIFICATION OF THE MARITIME CONTACT BEING REPORTED.

Name: ELNOT CONFIDENCE
Explanation: NUMERIC VALUE BETWEEN BETWEEN 1 (LOW) AND 10 (HIGH) INDICATING THE CONFIDENCE THAT AN OBSERVED SIGNAL AND AN ELECTRONIC NOTATION (ELNOT) HAVE BEEN CORRECTLY ASSOCIATED.

Name: ELEVATION CONFIDENCE LEVEL
Explanation: THE CONFIDENCE LEVEL, EXPRESSED AS A PERCENTAGE (00 TO 99) , THAT A SPECIFIC ELEVATION HAS BEEN VERTICALLY POSITIONED TO WITHIN A SPECIFIED VERTICAL ACCURACY.

Name: ELEVATION MSL CONFIDENCE LEVEL
Explanation: INDICATES THE CONFIDENCE LEVEL, EXPRESSED AS A PERCENTAGE, THAT A SPECIFIC GEOMETRIC SPATIAL ELEMENT, ELEVATION MEAN SEA LEVEL (MSL) LINEAR ACCURACY, HAS BEEN VERTICALLY POSITIONED TO WITHIN A SPECIFIED VERTICAL ACCURACY.

Name: COORDINATES RADIUS OF ACCURACY CONFIDENCE LEVEL
ELECTRONIC ATTACK CONFIDENCE LEVEL
Explanation: THE LEVEL OF CERTAINTY IN ELECTRONIC ATTACK INFORMATION REPORTED.

Name: ELECTRONIC PROTECTION CONFIDENCE LEVEL
Explanation: THE LEVEL OF CERTAINTY IN ELECTRONIC PROTECTION INFORMATION REPORTED.

Name: ELECTRONIC PROTECTION CREDIBILITY
Explanation: THE LEVEL OF CREDIBILITY OF ELECTRONIC PROTECTION INFORMATION REPORTED.

Name: RADAR WARNING RECEIVER CONFIDENCE
Explanation: THE CREDIBILITY OF RADAR WARNING RECEIVER INDICATIONS.
